523
00:31:39,108 --> 00:31:41,389
It's weird if everyone cares about your opinion.

524
00:31:41,510 --> 00:31:43,431
It's meaningful if one person cares a lot.

525
00:31:43,991 --> 00:31:47,234
But in order to actually pull this off, you need to be flexible about your choices.

526
00:31:50,524 --> 00:31:53,125
In Lady Killer, we developed a unique dialogue system.

527
00:31:53,346 --> 00:31:55,487
Choices appear as they occur to the protagonist,

528
00:31:55,527 --> 00:31:58,128
and they disappear as they're no longer relevant to the conversation.

529
00:31:58,628 --> 00:32:01,250
This gives a more naturalistic feeling to the pace of conversation,

530
00:32:01,590 --> 00:32:04,712
and it also gives us a lot of flexibility in how we build sets of choices.

531
00:32:06,232 --> 00:32:09,574
Players learn quickly that they don't always have to say something

532
00:32:09,594 --> 00:32:10,575
the moment a choice appears.

533
00:32:11,035 --> 00:32:12,716
